<!--template match = subSubSection[ancestor::treatment]--><tp:treatment-sec sec-type="diagnosis">
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Diagnosis
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Cixius verticalis</tp:taxon-name>
is the largest of the 
Madeira
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Cixius</tp:taxon-name>
(
<!--template match = tableCitation--><xref>Table 1</xref>
). The vertex is sharper on the anterior margin than in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. madeirensis</tp:taxon-name>
. The overall colouration is darker than in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. madeirensis</tp:taxon-name>
, with larger and darker wing punctuations. The lobes of the anal tube in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. verticalis</tp:taxon-name>
do not bend rostrally as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. madeirensis</tp:taxon-name>
. The aedeagus differs in the following characters: (1) the basal half of the velum shows a broad, hump-shaped dilatation; (2) the medioventral expansion of the base of the aedeagus is rounded or subtriangular and less pronounced than in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. madeirensis</tp:taxon-name>
.
</p>
</tp:treatment-sec>
