<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Redescription
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
BODY MEASUREMENTS (mm). 
Lectotype
: BL = 7.81, HW = 1.32, ML = 1.75, MW = 1.5, PW = 1.62, VL= 0.32. For other specimens see 
<!--template match = tableCitation--><xref>Table 1.</xref>
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
COLOURATION. Males like 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. wollastoni</tp:taxon-name>
<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->sp. nov.
but eyes pale yellow (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-7--189-232-1777-1803-">Figs 3C</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-12--189-232-1776-1802-">5B</xref>
), mesonotum glossy; the bands on the tegmina also similar, but vestigial; legs yellowish but the dark brown colour around the tibiofemoral joints extends like a shadow along the tibia. The females are darker than males, as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. wollastoni</tp:taxon-name>
<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->sp. nov.
, and the gonoplacs are light brown, being lighter towards the internal lateral margins (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-16--189-232-1812-1838-">Fig. 8C–D</xref>
).
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
HEAD. Forehead, vertex, and ocellus as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. wollastoni</tp:taxon-name>
<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->sp. nov.
but differs from this in the vertex that is more excavated, the anterior margin is more angular, and the parabola, on the posterior margin, is less pronounced (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">Fig. 7B</xref>
). Frons is approximately 1.1 times as wide as the height medially (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">Fig. 7A</xref>
).
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
THORAX. Pronotum, mesonotum, tegulae, tegmina, and tibiae as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. wollastoni</tp:taxon-name>
<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->sp. nov.
(
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-7--189-232-1777-1803-">Figs 3C</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-12--189-232-1776-1802-">5B</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">7A–B</xref>
).
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
MALE GENITALIA. Lateral lobes of the pygofer concave distally (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">Fig. 7C–D</xref>
). The anal tube is as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. wollastoni</tp:taxon-name>
<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->sp. nov.
but the ventrocaudal margin is slightly concave and divergent, its lobes are subtriangular, and the widest part is distinctly larger medially than at the base (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">Fig. 7F–H, J</xref>
). Lamella of paramere oval, the anterior margin is oblique, and the ventral and posterior margins are slightly concave (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">Fig. 7I</xref>
). Basal part of the aedeagus long and rectangular with a small rounded or subtriangular ventromedial projection (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">Fig. 7K–L</xref>
); the ventral spine at the proximal end is triangular; there are two thorns subapically; the right-side is large, variable in size, and sharply bends distally at a 90º angle; the left spine is almost straight and sometimes slightly curved, but much smaller and thinner than in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. madeirensis</tp:taxon-name>
(
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1780-1806-">Fig. 7M–N</xref>
).
</p>
