<!--template match = subSubSection[ancestor::treatment]--><tp:treatment-sec sec-type="distribution">
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Distribution and ecology
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Endemic to the island of Madeira. Due to the successive errors in identification, previous records of this species (Noualhier 1897; 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref18564">
China
1938
</xref>
; 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref19283">Lindberg 1941</xref>
, 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref19421">1961</xref>
), should be taken with caution. In this study, adults of this species were collected from medium to high altitudes on the slopes of northern Madeira. Adults can be found from April to October in endemic plants that grow in shaded and humid areas of the evergreen laurel forest, such as 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Persea indica</tp:taxon-name>
and 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Clethra arborea</tp:taxon-name>
trees, 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Euphorbia mellifera Aiton</tp:taxon-name>
shrubs and 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Diplazium caudatum (Cav.) Jermy</tp:taxon-name>
ferns. It was also found in hedges and trees that grow in the native forest (
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref19421">Lindberg 1961</xref>
).
</p>
</tp:treatment-sec>
